6753 if (end_level <= start_level) {
6754 return 0;
6755 }
6756
6757 // Outline of the optimization that uses options.files_size_error_margin.
6758 // When approximating the files total size that is used to store a keys range,
6759 // we first sum up the sizes of the files that fully fall into the range.
6760 // Then we sum up the sizes of all the files that may intersect with the range
6761 // (this includes all files in L0 as well). Then, if total_intersecting_size
6762 // is smaller than total_full_size * options.files_size_error_margin - we can
6763 // infer that the intersecting files have a sufficiently negligible
6764 // contribution to the total size, and we can approximate the storage required
6765 // for the keys in range as just half of the intersecting_files_size.
6766 // E.g., if the value of files_size_error_margin is 0.1, then the error of the
6767 // approximation is limited to only ~10% of the total size of files that fully
6768 // fall into the keys range. In such case, this helps to avoid a costly
6769 // process of binary searching the intersecting files that is required only
6770 // for a more precise calculation of the total size.
6771
6772 autovector<FdWithKeyRange*, 32> first_files;
6773 autovector<FdWithKeyRange*, 16> last_files;

6775 // scan all the levels

6781 }

6813 // (inferred from the sorted order)

6840 }

6843 // If the total_intersecting_size is less than X% of the total_full_size - we

6849 static_cast<uint64_t>(total_full_size * margin)) {
6850 total_full_size += total_intersecting_size / 2;
6851 } else {
6852 // Estimate for all the first files (might also be last files), at each
6853 // level

6602 // this new manifest later (which can happens in e.g, SyncWAL()), this new
6603 // manifest creates an illusion that such WAL hasn't been deleted.
6604 VersionEdit wal_deletions;
6605 wal_deletions.DeleteWalsBefore(min_log_number_to_keep());

6607 if (!wal_deletions.EncodeTo(&wal_deletions_record)) {
6608 return Status::Corruption("Unable to Encode VersionEdit: " +
6609 wal_deletions.DebugString(true));
6610 }
6611 io_s = log->AddRecord(write_options, wal_deletions_record);
6612 if (!io_s.ok()) {
6613 return io_s;
6614 }
6615
6616 for (auto cfd : *column_family_set_) {
6617 assert(cfd);
6618
6619 if (cfd->IsDropped()) {
6620 continue;
6621 }
6622 assert(cfd->initialized());

6624 // Store column family info
6625 VersionEdit edit;
6626 if (cfd->GetID() != 0) {
6627 // default column family is always there,
6628 // no need to explicitly write it
6629 edit.AddColumnFamily(cfd->GetName());
6630 edit.SetColumnFamily(cfd->GetID());
6631 }
6632 edit.SetComparatorName(
6633 cfd->internal_comparator().user_comparator()->Name());
6634 edit.SetPersistUserDefinedTimestamps(
6635 cfd->ioptions()->persist_user_defined_timestamps);
6636 std::string record;
6637 if (!edit.EncodeTo(&record)) {
6638 return Status::Corruption("Unable to Encode VersionEdit:" +
6639 edit.DebugString(true));
6640 }

6642 if (!io_s.ok()) {
6643 return io_s;
6644 }
6645 }
6646
6647 {
6648 // Save files
6649 VersionEdit edit;
6650 edit.SetColumnFamily(cfd->GetID());
6651
6652 const auto* current = cfd->current();
6653 assert(current);
6654
6655 const auto* vstorage = current->storage_info();
6656 assert(vstorage);
6657
6658 for (int level = 0; level < cfd->NumberLevels(); level++) {
6659 const auto& level_files = vstorage->LevelFiles(level);
6660
6661 for (const auto& f : level_files) {
6662 assert(f);
6663
6664 edit.AddFile(level, f->fd.GetNumber(), f->fd.GetPathId(),
6665 f->fd.GetFileSize(), f->smallest, f->largest,
6666 f->fd.smallest_seqno, f->fd.largest_seqno,
6667 f->marked_for_compaction, f->temperature,
6668 f->oldest_blob_file_number, f->oldest_ancester_time,
6669 f->file_creation_time, f->epoch_number, f->file_checksum,
6670 f->file_checksum_func_name, f->unique_id,
6671 f->compensated_range_deletion_size, f->tail_size,
6672 f->user_defined_timestamps_persisted);
6673 }
6674 }
6675
6676 edit.SetCompactCursors(vstorage->GetCompactCursors());
6677
6678 const auto& blob_files = vstorage->GetBlobFiles();
6679 for (const auto& meta : blob_files) {
6680 assert(meta);
6681
6682 const uint64_t blob_file_number = meta->GetBlobFileNumber();
6683
6684 edit.AddBlobFile(blob_file_number, meta->GetTotalBlobCount(),
6685 meta->GetTotalBlobBytes(), meta->GetChecksumMethod(),
6686 meta->GetChecksumValue());
6687 if (meta->GetGarbageBlobCount() > 0) {
6688 edit.AddBlobFileGarbage(blob_file_number, meta->GetGarbageBlobCount(),
6689 meta->GetGarbageBlobBytes());
6690 }
6691 }
6692
6693 const auto iter = curr_state.find(cfd->GetID());
6694 assert(iter != curr_state.end());
6695 uint64_t log_number = iter->second.log_number;
6696 edit.SetLogNumber(log_number);
6697
6698 if (cfd->GetID() == 0) {
6699 // min_log_number_to_keep is for the whole db, not for specific column
6700 // family. So it does not need to be set for every column family, just
6701 // need to be set once. Since default CF can never be dropped, we set
6702 // the min_log to the default CF here.
6703 uint64_t min_log = min_log_number_to_keep();
6704 if (min_log != 0) {
6705 edit.SetMinLogNumberToKeep(min_log);
6706 }
6707 }
6708
6709 const std::string& full_history_ts_low = iter->second.full_history_ts_low;
6710 if (!full_history_ts_low.empty()) {
6711 edit.SetFullHistoryTsLow(full_history_ts_low);
6712 }
6713
6714 edit.SetLastSequence(descriptor_last_sequence_);
6715
6716 const Comparator* ucmp = cfd->user_comparator();
6717 assert(ucmp);
6718 std::string record;
6719 if (!edit.EncodeTo(&record, ucmp->timestamp_size())) {
6720 return Status::Corruption("Unable to Encode VersionEdit:" +
6721 edit.DebugString(true));
6722 }
6723 io_s = log->AddRecord(write_options, record);
6724 if (!io_s.ok()) {
6725 return io_s;
6726 }
6727 }
6728 }
6729 return Status::OK();
